      "writtenOn": "2021-04-13T23:49:21Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "AsProject. It is related to switching to use Realms for authorization. Milo will authenticate the user, then check Milo *and* Buildbucket ACLs itself locally, then call Buildbucket using AsProject to actually fetch necessary data. This would allow to remove two complicated mechanisms: delegation tokens and https://cr-buildbucket.appspot.com/rpcexplorer/services/access.Access/ (and a caching layer around it).\n\n\"AsProject\" is a way to authorize calls between LUCI services (which mutually trust one another) done in a context of some LUCI project (but not a concrete user). It assumes LUCI services do ACL checks on the perimeter (and LUCI Realms provide a model where Milo can easily check Buildbucket ACLs if it needs to). \n\nThis is not final yet.",
      "parentUuid": "3aba97b0_29fd0395",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 136,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 136,
        "endChar": 26
      },
